Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer II* position with *Konami Gaming, Inc.* I bring over three years of professional experience designing and delivering full-stack backend systems, RESTful APIs, and CI/CD automation, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands — enterprise-grade RESTful APIs, CI/CD pipelines, SQL-backed services, and legacy system maintenance. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected enterprise-grade RESTful APIs across 1,000+ platform endpoints with entity-level access control, enforcing fine-grained authorization for safe and efficient data exchange across a distributed full-stack platform. I designed and automated CI/CD pipelines covering build, test, and deployment stages, applying JUnit-style unit testing and structured validation to maintain reliability at scale — directly mirroring the Jenkins and Gradle automation workflows central to this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, PostgreSQL, and Redis with SQL schema design, stored procedures, and query optimization — and contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with Spring Boot (Jersey-style RESTful APIs) and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications. I also maintained and enhanced legacy systems by debugging across multiple deployment configurations and adapting backend workflows to new infrastructure, and developed reporting solutions using parameterized SQL queries and dynamic report generation over PostgreSQL, reducing ticket resolution time by 20%. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to SYNKROS development — designing scalable full-stack features, securing enterprise APIs, optimizing reporting pipelines, and maintaining the reliability of a large-scale casino management system.

My research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in proof-of-concept prototyping and Unix/Linux-based system development — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and innovation-first culture Konami values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I researched, prototyped, and delivered proof-of-concept designs for facial recognition and OCR card scanning pipelines using PyTorch and CUDA on a Unix/Linux HPC cluster — the same kind of exploratory R&D that drives SYNKROS forward with new capabilities. I also configured relational data sources and parameterized query pipelines on Unix/Linux servers, ensuring secure and efficient model serving — reinforcing the database configuration and Unix environment skills this role requires.

I have always been passionate about pushing the limits of innovation and delivering quality in every detail — the very principles at the heart of Konami's mission — and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering the goal of delivering the highest and most enjoyable experiences possible through SYNKROS. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

